# corpact

Corporate actions collector, storage and public web dashboard — running on AWS free tier with CI/CD via GitHub Actions and Kubernetes (k3s).

## Architecture overview

```
Public APIs (SEC EDGAR, Yahoo Finance)
        │
   Lambda scraper (EventBridge daily)
        │
      SQS queue
        │
   Lambda processor → RDS PostgreSQL ← API pod (FastAPI)
                                              │
                                       Frontend pod (Next.js)
                                              │
                                         ALB → CloudFront → users
```

## Repository layout

```
corpact/
├── app/                    # Python backend
│   ├── api/                # FastAPI application
│   ├── worker/             # SQS consumer / normalizer
│   ├── core/               # Shared config, DB, logging
│   └── models/             # SQLAlchemy models + Pydantic schemas
├── frontend/               # Next.js dashboard
├── k8s/                    # Kubernetes manifests
├── infra/                  # Lambda functions + IaC notes
├── tests/                  # pytest suites
├── Dockerfile              # Multi-stage image (api + worker)
├── docker-compose.yml      # Local dev environment
└── .github/workflows/      # CI/CD pipeline
```

## Quick start (local)

```bash
cp .env.example .env          # fill in your values
docker compose up --build
# API:      http://localhost:8000/docs
# Frontend: http://localhost:3000
```

## Environment variables

See `.env.example` for all required variables.

## Deploying

Push to `main`. GitHub Actions handles build → test → ECR push → kubectl apply → smoke test.

See `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` for the full pipeline.

## Free tier limits to watch

| Service | Free allowance | This project's usage |
|---------|---------------|----------------------|
| Lambda  | 1M req/month  | ~60 invocations/day  |
| RDS t3.micro | 750 hrs/month | 1 instance |
| ECR | 500 MB | ~220 MB image |
| S3 | 5 GB | raw event archive |
| CloudFront | 1 TB egress | dashboard traffic |
